  "text": "To be as comprehensive as possible in adjusting for factors that might affect outcome, we identified 62 covariates (Table 1) . A combined weighted comorbidity index was used to quantify each individual's burden of comorbidity. The combined weighted comorbidity index developed by Gagne et al [CITATION_1] is a summary score that combines the Charlson Index with the Elixhauser system, and was found to have better mortality predictability than either the Charlson or the Elixhauser system. ",
